	   <tr><td colspan=2>yes playing a mage is hard but very rewarding.i have a 46th lvl and have not experienced a great degree of diff in getting in a group.we can deal out a great deal of non-melee damage and also provide the group with another tank,a 2 for one deal.soloing is a great way to learn you abilities and the pets also,and can make good exp but i think grouping exp is faster due to less down time medding.the pet issue is a touch one which we could debate all day long.i am in dreadlands right now and the fire pet is very good.for the caster situation think air for stun,and earth for solo with fireshild and burnout ofcourse.well got to go fight safe and hard friends.&nbsp;&nbsp; jojan 46th season<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
