	   <tr><td colspan=2>The most important thing you should have in an int caster is Intelligence but the other stats are also important as you will not always have stat buffing equips at the beginning of the game unless you are a *twink*.<br><br>Also another thing you need is Faction, just ask any high end player of the game, and as we all know the Inkies faction sucks. They make great mages but they are also KoS in most places where you need to buy spells.<br><br>As the poster before me said, the Erudites are a stupid looking race, but they are also the best casters in the game. They also have not the greatest faction with the other races of Norrath.<br><br>That leaves us now with the Gnomes and High Elves. Dont get me wrong but they are the best races to start out with as Mages as they are both on good faction and they also both have a base Int of over 100. And the 6 point difference wont really matter as you can get higher end gear cheaper these days as the economy is totally screwed. Yuo should put at least put 20 or all of your points in Int still as that will matter. Most players recommend all but I only recommend 20 as you also need other stats to survive since you will solo&nbsp;&nbsp;until probably about 45 or higher.<br><br>Also as a mage with a pet you will be able to take down low red mobs and lower past level 8 since the level 4 pets arent all that great. But at 8 you will also need lots of pps since you will shell out about 30pps on spells at 90 cha and amiable faction. Dont get me wrong though these spells are not even near a ripoff as they will do about 3-4 times damage what the level 4 spells did. Also your pet just about doubles in power here.<br><br>Your starting religion also matters on your faction and it will affect you in some ways, but as the great Zuranthium said, this is really not a factor to be concerned with.<br><br>Thank you if you took the time to read this post and good day to all.<br><br>Dalaan Ogrebane           Dallaan