	   <tr><td colspan=2>I recommend joining a group when it's just forming. that way you have less chance of hoping in only to have the group disband 15 min later, wasting in essence all your time to run to them and then have to find another group later.<br><br>Also as groups go consider just getting into a group of 2-3 every now and then. Easy to form, less down time then if you solo'd, you should pull about 4-5 times faster (so even with the smaller then 6 xp bonus you'll make more on average then you would soloing).<br><br>Also never forget the biggest edge of a group... decreased chance of dying. Specially if your a mage. Look... your pet is nice, but NOTHING compared to a real tank one on one at their level. If the pet is attacking the mob, and the tanks are attacking the mob... the odds of it agging on you and not being taunted off are much smaller.<br><br>Ow and don't forget your damage sheild. ALWAYS keep that up on the tank as long as the MoB's still attacking.<br><br>Final note... Earth and Water pets are nice soloing, but Fire and Air rule grouping. This is one of the few times the Fire pet really shine. He hits harder then the other pets, which is finally useful since in grouping scenarios he's like a guided missile, and he won't be taking all the damage so his low Hp aren't too bad, specially if you buff him.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
